This problem is caused by attempting to deploy the org.eclipse.emf.exampes.library example plug-ins into an Eclipse 3.1 environment.  These plug-ins target Eclipse 3.2, which uses the Eclipse-LazyStart header instead of Eclipse-AutoStart in the OSGi bundle manifest.

In an Eclipse 3.1 runtime, the org.eclipse.emf.examples.library.edit plug-in will not auto-start, causing the symptoms reported in this defect.

To work around this, simply replace "Eclipse-LazyStart" with "Eclipse-AutoStart" in the MANIFEST.MF files of the following plug-ins:
  - org.eclipse.emf.examples.library
  - org.eclipse.emf.examples.library.edit
  - org.eclipse.emf.examples.library.editor
